Keycloak can be accessed:

* Within your cluster, at the following DNS name at port 80:

  keycloak-http.reportnet.svc.cluster.local

* From outside the cluster, run these commands in the same shell:

  export POD_NAME=$(kubectl get pods --namespace reportnet -l app=keycloak,release=keycloak -o jsonpath="{.items[0].metadata.name}")
  echo "Visit http://127.0.0.1:8080 to use Keycloak"
  kubectl port-forward --namespace reportnet $POD_NAME 8080
